The '''Animal Rights Party''' ({{lang-de|Tierrechtspartei}}, TRP) is an [[animal welfare]] [[political party]] in [[Austria]]. It is led by [[Ralph Chaloupek]].<ref name="Lansford2013">{{cite book|author=Tom Lansford|title=Political Handbook of the World 2013|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=lUF1AwAAQBAJ&pg=PA90|accessdate=18 September 2014|date=15 April 2013|publisher=SAGE Publications|isbn=978-1-4522-5825-6|page=90}}</ref> It contested the [[Lower Austrian state election, 2008|Lower Austrian state election]] (although only in [[Mödling]], where it got 854 votes and became the strongest minor party with 1.34% locally).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.news.at/articles/0833/11/215682/drei-listen-unterschriften-von-tierschutz-migration-nr-wahlen|title=Drei neue Listen sammeln Unterschriften: Von Tierschutz bis Migration bei NR-Wahlen|work=News|date=13 August 2008|accessdate=7 June 2012}}</ref> It also contested the [[Austrian legislative election, 2008|2008 national election]], but only in [[Vienna]].

