{{Use Australian English|date=August 2016}}
The '''Australian Bill of Rights Group''' was a minor Australian political party agitating for the creation of a [[Bill of rights|Bill of Rights]] for Australia. Formally registered on 19 December 1995, it operated until it was deregistered for having fewer than 500 members on 15 November 1999.<ref>[[Australian Electoral Commission]]. [http://www.aec.gov.au/Parties_and_Representatives/Party_Registration/Deregistered_parties/abrg.htm Australian Bill of Rights Group]</ref> At the [[Australian federal election, 1996|1996 federal election]] it contested the [[Australian Senate|Senate]] in New South Wales, Victoria and Queensland on joint tickets with the [[Republican Party of Australia]]; among its candidates were future [[New South Wales Legislative Council]]lor [[Peter Breen (Australian politician)|Peter Breen]], who headed the ticket in New South Wales. The party ran a single ticket in Victoria in the [[Australian federal election, 1998|1998 federal election]].

